modelDescription: BidAsk is a slice of bytes that represents the bids or asks for a given product. The term "bid" refers to the highest price a buyer will pay to buy a specified number of shares of a stock at any given time. The term "ask" refers to the lowest price at which a seller will sell the stock. The bid price will almost always be lower than the ask or “offer,” price.
customUnmarshaler: func (ba *BidAsk) UnmarshalJSON(b []byte) error { *ba = BidAsk(b); return nil; }
